<section class="case-overview">
<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>A home business owner from West Pennant Hills brought in their iMac 27-inch that had become extremely slow and was showing <a href="/macbook-startup-errors/">startup errors</a>. The Fusion Drive had partially failed—the HDD component was dying while the SSD portion still worked. This caused boot problems and data corruption. We recovered all data and upgraded to a fast NVMe SSD, transforming the machine's performance.</p>
</section>

<section class="case-symptoms">
<h2>Initial Symptoms</h2>
<ul>
